7. Conclusion and Future Work
This paper presents and verifies a complete three-layer lightweight hardware security SoC targeting Fabless tapeout on the open-source SKY130 process. Core module simulation achieves 100% pass rates (39/39 test cases), zero latches, zero timing violations, meeting all ChipFoundry tapeout acceptance criteria. Tapeout submission (CI2609) is planned for Q2 2026.

Future work includes: (1) Physical synthesis via OpenLane RTL-to-GDSII flow; (2) Static Timing Analysis (STA) and physical verification (DRC/LVS); (3) Post-silicon bring-up — PUF statistical characterization (Hamming distance distribution, inter-chip uniqueness, intra-chip reliability vs. temperature/voltage); (4) Integration with a RISC-V processor core to form a complete hardware Root of Trust platform; (5) Exploration of post-quantum-resistant hash functions as a replacement for the ARX engine.

